      "span_text": "This agrees with similar but less direct probability estimates for evoked vesicle fusion at active zones of NMJs in human and rat muscles and on phasic muscle fibers in lizard muscles (Ϸ6%), where we predict that the AZM like the presynaptic membrane macromolecules at the active zones has a bilateral distribution relative to docked vesicles, and it is 10-fold greater than probability estimates for NMJs in frog and on tonic muscle fibers of the lizard, where the AZM and membrane macromolecules have a unilateral arrangement relative to the docked vesicles."
